gomodel:SYNGO_5318  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Figure 4: In vitro analysis showing the interaction of PDZ domains of PSD95 (DLG4) with Sema4C. In cerebral cortex, these proteins also coimmunoprecipitate (Fig. 7a).\n\nFigure 6: Sema4C and PSD95 (DLG4) are enriched in PSD biochemical fractions prepared from cerebral cortex tissue.\n\nFigure 7c: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for Sema4C and PSD-95 (DLG4) in cultured cortical neurons showed co-localization in synaptic puncta.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Synaptosomal membrane and PSD (PSD1 and 2) fractions were prepared from the cerebral cortex of adult mice as previously described (26, 30) with minor modifications.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Antibodies to S4C were raised in rabbits against the product of pGEX5X1 S4Ccd, which is the C-terminal cytoplasmic domain of S4C. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5318" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

